DPV with high sensitivity was adopted as a kind of technique and method for the detection of calycosin standard solution with different concentration by PAGD/GCE. As shown in Fig. 5
                        (A and B), a good linear relationship between the concentration of calycosin and the oxidation peak current at 1.1 × 10−5–3.52 × 10−4 mol/L, and the linear regression equation as Ip (A) = 0.04848C (mol/L) − 3.2201 × 10−5 (R2 = 0.9925). The detection limit was 9.8 × 10−6 mol/L (S/N = 3). This method had the same and even better result than other reported methods (Table 1
                        ).
